It’s 2015--have the browser use real small-caps if the font supports them. Even if it doesn’t, you’re probably better off letting the browser make them instead of you creating them.<p><pre><code>    font-feature-settings: “smcp”;
</code></pre>
on an element turns lowercase letters into small-caps;<p><pre><code>    font-feature-settings: “c2sc”;
</code></pre>
turns uppercase letters into small-caps.<p>More at <a href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts/#font-variant-caps-prop" rel="nofollow">https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts/#font-variant-caps-prop</a>.<p>Safari’s renderring engine WebKit just got font-feature-settings: support: <a href="https://twitter.com/webkit/status/631827777319256064" rel="nofollow">https://twitter.com/webkit/status/631827777319256064</a>.
